[Patient] What exercises can I do to help with my heart failure?
[Educator] Walking or jogging in your safe neighborhood can be a good start for your heart health.
[Patient] I don't have money for a gym membership, what should I do?
[Educator] You can try free activities like walking in the park or doing household chores to stay active.
[Patient] I'm not sure if I have the time or energy to exercise regularly.
[Educator] Start small with short walks or incorporating movement into your daily routine for better heart health.
[Patient] How can I stay motivated to exercise with all my other responsibilities?
[Educator] Find activities you enjoy, set small goals, and remember the benefits of exercise for your heart.